speech.p:
asked the Minister of Health (1) if he will publish in the OFFICIAL REPORT details, including cost, of the cuts to be made in the proposed expenditure for 1967 on workshops, social centres and hostels for the mentally ill as a result of the £3 million cut in proposed expenditure in 1967 on local authority health and welfare services, which were published on 25th July of this year;

(2) if he will publish in the OFFICIAL REPORT details, including cost, of the cuts to be made in the proposed expenditure for 1967 on centres and homes for elderly, including the elderly mentally

infirm, as a result of the £3 million cut in proposed expenditure in 1967 on local authority health and welfare services, which were published on 25th July of this year.

p.q:
That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to regulate fee-charging employment agencies, it is expedient to authorise—


(a) the payment out of moneys provided by Parliament of any administrative expenses incurred by the Minister of Labour in consequence of that Act, including expenses attributable to proceedings under that Act;

(b) the payment into the Exchequer of fees received by him in pursuance thereof.—[Mr. Gunter.]
